  "details": "Mozilla Firefox is a standalone web browser, designed for standards compliance and performance.  Its functionality can be enhanced via a plethora of extensions.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):Mozilla Firefox is an open-source web browser, designed for standards compliance, performance and portability.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nThrough complicated navigations with new windows, an HTTP page could have inherited a secure lock icon from an HTTPS page. This vulnerability affects Firefox ESR &lt; 78.10, Thunderbird &lt; 78.10, and Firefox &lt; 88.(CVE-2021-23998)\r\n\r\nRequests initiated through reader mode did not properly omit cookies with a SameSite attribute. This vulnerability affects Thunderbird &lt; 91.9, Firefox ESR &lt; 91.9, and Firefox &lt; 100.(CVE-2022-29912)",
